ORDER BY ?zone ?propLabel

PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>

# Retrieve ALC and MPC endpoints for zone properties that are not editable
SELECT DISTINCT ?zone ?property ?endpoint ?endpointType WHERE {
  # zones and their properties
  ?zone a brick:Zone .
  ?zone brick:hasPart ?property .

  # the property must be a Zone Property (or any subclass)
  ?property a ?propClass .
  FILTER(?propClass = brick:Zone_Property || EXISTS { ?propClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone_Property })

  # property is marked as not editable (assume a boolean literal)
  ?property brick:isEditable ?editable .
  FILTER(?editable = false)

  # endpoints attached to the property
  ?property brick:hasEndpoint ?endpoint .
  ?endpoint a ?endpointType .
  FILTER(?endpointType = brick:ALC_Endpoint || ?endpointType = brick:MPC_Endpoint)
}
ORDER BY ?zone ?property ?endpointType

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='sparql_query', args='{"query": "PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.1/Brick#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?label ?endpoint\\nWHERE {\\n  # Identify properties\\n  ?property a rdf:Property .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?label . }\\n  # Property must be marked read\\u2011only\\n  ?property brick:readOnly true .\\n  # The property is associated (directly or via subclass) with a Zone or a Room\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zoneClass .\\n    ?zoneClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?roomClass .\\n    ?roomClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Room .\\n  }\\n  # Follow possible sh:property (chained connections) that link back to Zone/Room\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?shape sh:property ?shProp .\\n    ?shProp sh:path ?property ;\\n           sh:class ?zoneClass .\\n    ?zoneClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n  # External reference endpoints of interest (alc or mpc)\\n  ?property brick:externalReference ?extRef .\\n  ?extRef brick:endpoint ?endpoint .\\n  FILTER(?endpoint = \\"alc\\" || ?endpoint = \\"mpc\\")\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-603547940f49489b855f2ce8bbcabc2b', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 37, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

  # Find properties that point to an external endpoint
  ?rtu ?property ?endpoint .
  
  # The endpoint must be of type ALC or MPC

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\n\\n# Retrieve ALC and MPC endpoints for zone properties that are not editable\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?zone ?property ?endpoint ?endpointType WHERE {\\n  # zones and their properties\\n  ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  ?zone brick:hasPart ?property .\\n\\n  # the property must be a Zone Property (or any subclass)\\n  ?property a ?propClass .\\n  FILTER(?propClass = brick:Zone_Property || EXISTS { ?propClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone_Property })\\n\\n  # property is marked as not editable (assume a boolean literal)\\n  ?property brick:isEditable ?editable .\\n  FILTER(?editable = false)\\n\\n  # endpoints attached to the property\\n  ?property brick:hasEndpoint ?endpoint .\\n  ?endpoint a ?endpointType .\\n  FILTER(?endpointType = brick:ALC_Endpoint || ?endpointType = brick:MPC_Endpoint)\\n}\\nORDER BY ?zone ?property ?endpointType"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-7b03194abf33410f8cb9def76742da18', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 38, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

PREFIX ref: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX s223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?target ?prop ?label ?qty ?ref ?alc_endpoint ?mpc_endpoint where {
?target a s223:WatertoWaterHeatPump .
?target s223:contains ?prop .
?prop rdfs:label ?label .
?prop s223:observes ?qty .
?qty s223:hasExternalReference ?ref .
?ref ref:endpoint ?alc_endpoint .
?ref ref:mpc_db_name ?mpc_endpoint .
?ref ref:writable "False" .
}

ModelResponse(parts=[TextPart(content='{\n  "sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sd: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?propLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  ?zone a sd:Zone .\\n  ?zone sd:hasProperty ?prop .\\n  ?prop brick:writable false .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel . }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:endpoint ?alcEndpoint . }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:mpc_db_name ?mpcEndpoint . }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?propLabel"\n}', part_kind='text')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 37, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>\\nPREFIX sd: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?propLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Find zones\\n  ?zone a sd:Zone .\\n  # Their associated properties\\n  ?zone sd:hasProperty ?prop .\\n  # Property is marked as non-writable\\n  ?prop brick:writable ?writable .\\n  FILTER(?writable = false)\\n  # Get optional label and endpoints\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel . }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:endpoint ?alcEndpoint . }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:mpc_db_name ?mpcEndpoint . }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?propLabel"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-3cf89f8e3e5b4c9299c543d31c136d68', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 37, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[TextPart(content='{\n  "sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>\\nPREFIX d223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?rtu ?property ?endpoint\\nWHERE {\\n  # Find RTU instances (any class name containing \\"RTU\\")\\n  ?rtu a ?rtuClass .\\n  FILTER(CONTAINS(LCASE(STR(?rtuClass)), \\"rtu\\"))\\n\\n  # RTU has a property (Brick model)\\n  ?rtu brick:hasProperty ?property .\\n\\n  # The property has an endpoint (control point) and a writability flag\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property brick:endpoint ?endpoint }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property brick:writable ?writable }\\n\\n  # Keep only read‑only properties (writable explicitly false or absent)\\n  FILTER( (!BOUND(?writable)) || (?writable = false) )\\n}\\nORDER BY ?rtu ?property"\n}', part_kind='text')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 38, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

PREFIX ref: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX s223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?target ?prop ?label ?qty ?ref ?alc_endpoint ?mpc_endpoint where {
?target a s223:WatertoWaterHeatPump .
?target s223:contains ?prop .
?prop rdfs:label ?label .
?prop s223:observes ?qty .
?qty s223:hasExternalReference ?ref .
?ref ref:endpoint ?alc_endpoint .
?ref ref:mpc_db_name ?mpc_endpoint .
?ref ref:writable "False" .
}
